snippet.title: Global Game Jam 2016: Bunny Beats Gameplay Trailer
snippet.description:
“Have you ever stared at the moon and seen a bunny making mochi?”

Help your bunny friends craft mochi for the moon goddess Chang'e in this fast-paced rhythm game! Get into the groove and master each rabbit's unique beats in a musical mochi-making experience that's out of this world.

Get the game at http://globalgamejam.org/2016/games/bunny-beats

Credits:

Design:
- Brett Yang
- David Song
- Jeffrey Hsu
- Rohan Jalalizadeh
- Sirish Veligati
- Yi Zhu

Programming:
- Brett Yang

Writing:
- Yi Zhu

Sound/Music:
- David Song
- “Fly Me to the Moon” orig. by Bart Howard

Art/Graphics:
- Jeffrey Hsu
- Yi Zhu

Voice Talent:
- Sayuri Sakurada
- Yi Zhu

#ggj2016 #stlgamejam
